# ripgrep config — sourced via RIPGREP_CONFIG_PATH (set in ~/.zshrc).
# Catppuccin Mocha match colors to match the fzf / eza / bat palette.
# Color values are R,G,B triples (truecolor).

# match = Mocha red (#f38ba8), bold
--colors=match:fg:243,139,168
--colors=match:style:bold
# file paths = Mocha blue (#89b4fa)
--colors=path:fg:137,180,250
# line numbers = Mocha yellow (#f9e2af)
--colors=line:fg:249,226,175
# column numbers = Mocha mauve (#cba6f7)
--colors=column:fg:203,166,247

# --- behavior (commented: uncomment if you want it) ---
# smart-case: case-insensitive unless the pattern has an uppercase letter.
# This is a BEHAVIOR change from rg's case-sensitive default — opt in here.
# --smart-case
